 all leaders of the insurgency, and places it within a larger global and comparative framework. Examining such variables as gender, class, age, and power relationships, this book offers a sophisticated consideration of how ethnic nationalism and identity functioned in the United States during the 1960s and 1970s.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aChicano movementzCaliforniazLos Angeles. 0aCivil rights movementszCaliforniazLos AngelesxHistoryy20th century. 0aMexican AmericansxCivil rightszCaliforniazLos AngelesxHistoryy20th century. 0aMexican AmericanszCaliforniazLos AngelesxEthnic identity. 0aMexican AmericanszCaliforniazLos AngelesxPolitics and governmenty20th century. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / West (AK, CA, CO, HI, ID, MT, NV, UT, WY).2bisacsh  a1960s.  a1970s.  abrown berets.  achicana.  achicano movement.  achicano.  aclass.  aclassism.  acultural history.  acultural studies.  aethnic identity.  agender studies.  aglobal.  alatin america.  alatin american history.  alatin american.  alatinx.  alos angeles.  amexican culture.  amexican heritage.  amexico city.  anationalism.  areformation.  areformers.  aregional history.  asocial history.  asocial studies.  asouth america.  asouthern california.  awest coast.  awestern states.  awestern united states.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093596940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520935969423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520935969/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles